2.876 billion up 12 percentfrom the previous year's $2.576 billion.andP;  Earnings amounted to $252.8 millionor $3.19 a share up 4 percent from the previous year.andP;  Included in theearnings is a $110 million one time charge on transition that includes aworkforce reduction of 1500 people over a three year period.andM;[] DELPHI INFORMATION systems reported results for the third quarter endingDec. 31, 1989.andP;  The company, which specializes in turnkey informationsystems, earned $87,000 or two cents a share compared with a loss of $125,000for the same period during the prior year.andP;  Revenues for the period amountedto $5.181 million a slight decrease from the $5.474 reported the year before.andO;For the nine months, the company lost $391,000 while revenues reached $15.249million.andM;[] NASHUA reported earnings of $6.4 million for the fourth quarter whichended Dec. 31, 1989 against revenues of $232 million, slightly down from theprevious year.andP;  For the year ending Dec.31, 1989, Nashua saw revenues reach$946 million against earnings of $20.1 million.andM;[] NBI, the word processing concern reported a loss of $25.6 million or $2.99per common share for the second quarter ending Dec. 31, 1989.andP;  This compareswith a loss of $5.8 million for same period of the prior year.andP;  For the firstsix months, the company had a net loss of $32.8 million from continuingoperations.andP;  Recently, NBI concluded an agreement with Frame Informatique ofFrance for a French version of Legend, NBI's word processing program for theMicrosoft Windows environment.andM;(Peter Vekinis/19900206)</TEXT></DOC>